Here is all the R code needed to generate the figures used in the draft manuscript entitled âAssembly methods for nanopore-based metagenomic sequencing: an evaluation.â The project consist on downloading the data generated by Nicholls et al. (2019), subsampling the datasets in order to obtain a typical MinION output (3 and 6 Gbps), and use different assemblers for evaluating the state-of-art.

All the data needed for the figures is distributed in different CSV files generated from the original table provided by Pascual.

Figure 1

A. Even Mock Community statistics for each assembler.

I want to create a Figure similar to Figure 1 of Goldstein et al. (2019), in which we can observe the performance of each assembler in a visual way.

  1. Load the data.
library(ggpubr)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Loading required package: magrittr
d.fig1 = read.csv2(file = "./Fig1.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",", dec = ".")
d.fig1$N50 = d.fig1$N50 / 1000
d.fig1
  1. Generate the Figures.

We will try to separate each Figure in grids.

TIME

library(ggplot2)
p <- ggplot(d.fig1, aes(x = Time, y = Assembler)) + geom_point(aes(colour = Output)) + xlab("Time (s)") + ylab("")
p = p + theme_bw()
p

Creo que lo voy a separar en 3 y 6 Gbps porque si no va a ser demasiado. QuizÃ¡s aquÃ­ sÃ­ que convenga usar un grid.

p <- ggplot(data=d.fig2.1, aes(x=Assembler, y=Fraction, fill=Genome)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", color="black", position=position_dodge()) +
  theme_bw() + ylab("Metagenome Assembled Fraction (%)") + xlab("") + expand_limits(y=c(0, 100)) + facet_grid(rows = 
                                                                                                          vars(Output),
                                                                                                          cols = 
                                                                                                          vars(Genome)) 
p
## Warning: Removed 113 rows containing missing values (geom_bar).

p <- ggplot(data=d.fig2.1, aes(x=Output, y=Fraction, fill=Genome)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", color="black", position=position_dodge(), show.legend = FALSE) +
  theme_bw() + ylab("Metagenome Assembled Fraction (%)") + xlab("") + expand_limits(y=c(0, 105)) + 
  facet_grid(rows = vars(Assembler), cols = vars(Genome)) +
  geom_text(aes(label=Mean_Fraction), vjust=-0.3, color="black", size=2.5)
p
